Issues.Body:
Allow drop targets to display the drag image while the cursor is over the target and add support for setting drop descriptions.

<!-- Please read CONTRIBUTING.md before submitting a pull request -->

A possible implementation for #5884.


## Proposed changes

- Keep the scope to just drop targets, with support for displaying drag-images and setting drop descriptions.

- Maintain the current default `DropTarget` behavior. By default, do not display the drag-image or drop description.

- Add 3 new public DragEventArgs properties; `DropIcon`, `Message`, and `Insert`.

```csharp
namespace System.Windows.Forms
{
  public class DragEventArgs : EventArgs
  {
      /// <summary>
      /// Gets or sets the drop description icon type.
      /// </summary>
      public DropIconType DropIcon { get; set; }
  
      /// <summary>
      /// Gets or sets the drop description text such as "Move to %1".
      /// </summary>
      /// <remarks>
      /// <para>UI coloring is applied to the text in Insert if used by specifying %1 in Message.</para>
      /// </remarks>
      public string Message { get; set; }
  
      /// <summary>
      /// Gets or sets the drop description text such as "Documents" when %1 is specified in Message.
      /// </summary>
      /// <remarks>
      /// <para>UI coloring is applied to the text in Insert if used by specifying %1 in Message.</para>
      /// </remarks>
      public string Insert { get; set; }
  }
}
```

- Add a new public enumeration; `DropIconType`.

```csharp
namespace System.Windows.Forms
{
    /// <summary>
    ///  Specifies the drop description icon type.
    /// </summary>
    public enum DropIconType
    {
        /// <summary>
        /// No drop icon preference; use the default icon.
        /// </summary>
        Invalid = -1,

        /// <summary>
        /// A red bisected circle such as that found on a "no smoking" sign.
        /// </summary>
        None = 0,

        /// <summary>
        /// A plus sign (+) that indicates a copy operation.
        /// </summary>
        Copy = DragDropEffects.Copy,

        /// <summary>
        /// An arrow that indicates a move operation.
        /// </summary>
        Move = DragDropEffects.Move,

        /// <summary>
        /// An arrow that indicates a link.
        /// </summary>
        Link = DragDropEffects.Link,

        /// <summary>
        /// A tag icon that indicates that the metadata will be changed.
        /// </summary>
        Label = 6,

        /// <summary>
        /// A yellow exclamation mark that indicates that a problem has been encountered in the operation.
        /// </summary>
        Warning = 7,

        /// <summary>
        /// Windows 7 and later. Use no drop image.
        /// </summary>
        NoImage = 8
    }
}
```

- During the DragEnter event, if the application specifies a `DropIconType`, display the drag image and drop description.

- Add an internal `DragDropHelper` class to help manage the retrieval of the `IDropTargetHelper` interface pointer and expose the methods necessary to display the drag image, and provide methods to get and set the drop description.

- Add a drag-and-drop functional test form to the _WinformsControlsTest_ project with files for testing drag-and-drop operations.

